FPUS53 KPAH 131825
ZFPPAH

Zone Forecast Product
National Weather Service Paducah KY
1223 PM CST Sat Dec 13 2025

KYZ005-132200-
McCracken-
Including the city of Paducah
1223 PM CST Sat Dec 13 2025

...COLD WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT CST
/1 AM EST/ TONIGHT TO NOON CST  /1 PM EST/ SUNDAY...

.THIS AFTERNOON...Mostly cloudy with a slight chance of drizzle
and snow. Highs in the upper 30s. North winds 5 to 10 mph. Chance
of snow 20 percent.
.TONIGHT...Mostly cloudy in the evening, then becoming partly
cloudy. Colder with lows around 11. North winds around 10 mph.
.SUNDAY...Sunny. Much cooler with highs around 19. North winds
5 to 10 mph.
.SUNDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Cold with lows around 10 above.
Northeast winds around 5 mph in the evening, becoming light and
variable.
.MONDAY...Sunny. Not as cool with highs in the mid 30s. South
winds 5 to 10 mph.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Lows in the mid 20s.
.TUESDAY...Mostly sunny. Highs in the upper 40s.
.TUESDAY NIGHT AND WEDNESDAY...Mostly cloudy. Lows in the mid
30s. Highs in the mid 50s.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT...Mostly cloudy with a chance of showers. Lows
in the mid 40s. Temperature rising into the lower 50s after
midnight. Chance of rain 50 percent.
.THURSDAY...Cloudy with showers in the morning, then partly sunny
with a chance of showers in the afternoon. Highs around 60.
Temperature falling into the mid 50s in the afternoon. Chance of
rain 80 percent.
.THURSDAY NIGHT AND FRIDAY...Partly cloudy. Lows in the upper
20s. Highs in the mid 40s.

$$

INZ086-132200-
Vanderburgh-
Including the city of Evansville
1223 PM CST Sat Dec 13 2025

...COLD WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT CST
/1 AM EST/ TONIGHT TO NOON CST  /1 PM EST/ SUNDAY...

.THIS AFTERNOON...Cloudy with a 40 percent chance of snow. Highs
in the mid 30s. Temperature falling into the upper 20s. North
winds 5 to 10 mph.
.TONIGHT...Cloudy with a slight chance of snow in the evening,
then partly cloudy after midnight. Much colder with lows around
6 above. North winds 10 to 15 mph. Chance of snow 20 percent.
Wind chill readings as low as 4 below after midnight.
.SUNDAY...Sunny. Much colder with highs around 14. North winds
10 to 15 mph. Wind chill readings as low as 8 below in the
morning.
.SUNDAY NIGHT...Clear, cold with lows around 7 above. North winds
around 5 mph, becoming southeast after midnight.
.MONDAY...Sunny. Not as cool with highs in the mid 30s. Southwest
winds 5 to 10 mph.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Not as cool with lows in the mid
20s.
.TUESDAY...Mostly sunny. Highs in the mid 40s.
.TUESDAY NIGHT AND WEDNESDAY...Mostly cloudy. Lows in the mid
30s. Highs around 50.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT...Mostly cloudy. A chance of showers after
midnight. Lows in the lower 40s. Temperature rising to around
50 after midnight. Chance of rain 50 percent.
.THURSDAY...Cloudy with showers in the morning, then partly sunny
with a chance of showers in the afternoon. Highs in the upper
50s. Temperature falling into the lower 50s in the afternoon.
Chance of rain 90 percent.
.THURSDAY NIGHT AND FRIDAY...Partly cloudy. Lows in the upper
20s. Highs in the lower 40s.

$$

KYZ019-132200-
Daviess-
Including the city of Owensboro
1223 PM CST Sat Dec 13 2025

...COLD WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT CST
/1 AM EST/ TONIGHT TO NOON CST  /1 PM EST/ SUNDAY...

.THIS AFTERNOON...Cloudy with a 20 percent chance of snow. Highs
in the mid 30s. Northwest winds 5 to 10 mph.
.TONIGHT...Mostly cloudy. A chance of snow in the evening. Much
colder with lows around 8 above. North winds 10 to 15 mph. Chance
of snow 30 percent. Wind chill readings as low as 2 below after
midnight.
.SUNDAY...Sunny. Much cooler with highs around 15. North winds
10 to 15 mph. Wind chill readings as low as 6 below in the
morning.
.SUNDAY NIGHT...Clear, cold with lows around 7 above. North winds
around 5 mph in the evening, becoming light and variable.
.MONDAY...Sunny. Not as cool with highs in the mid 30s. South
winds 10 to 15 mph.
.MONDAY NIGHT...Mostly clear. Not as cool with lows in the lower
20s.
.TUESDAY...Mostly sunny. Highs in the mid 40s.
.TUESDAY NIGHT AND WEDNESDAY...Mostly cloudy. Lows in the mid
30s. Highs around 50.
.WEDNESDAY NIGHT...Mostly cloudy. Showers likely after midnight.
Lows in the lower 40s. Temperature rising to around 50 after
midnight. Chance of rain 60 percent.
.THURSDAY...Showers. Highs in the upper 50s. Chance of rain
90 percent.
.THURSDAY NIGHT...Partly cloudy. A chance of rain showers in the
evening. Lows in the upper 20s. Chance of rain 30 percent.
.FRIDAY...Mostly sunny. Cooler with highs in the lower 40s.

$$

